  "text": "HomeStyleShe bundled up in a black puffer coat to go snow tubing at the Invictus Games.Photo: Karwai Tang/WireImageEver since announcing her engagement to Prince Harry, the world's eyes have been fixed on Meghan Markle — and her style. We'll be following the Meghan Markle Effect™ with our column, \"Meghan Markle Wore a Thing.\"Prince Harry and Meghan Markle have been attending the Invictus Games this week in Whistler, British Columbia, which has brought us a slew of bundled up winter fashion moments from the duo. On Tuesday, the couple enjoyed a sunny day by going snow tubing — so of course, the Duchess of Sussex took the opportunity to wear yet another puffer coat, this time the Aritzia Super Puff Long Climatte Coat in black. (She had previously worn a white one by Mackage. Room in your luggage for not one, but two, giant puffers? Luxurious.) She layered the puffer over a cream cowl neck sweater by Rag \u0026 Bone, white skinny jeans and Sorel boots (Joan of Arctic Women's Waterproof Boots in taupe — which she also wore previously in a different, darker colorway).Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesPhoto: Samir Hussein/WireImageTo top things off, Markle kept it cozy with a black cableknit hat by Moncler and black-and-gold sunglasses by Miu Miu.See more of our favorite looks from the Duchess of Sussex in the gallery below:Please note: Occasionally, we use affiliate links on our site. In no way does this affect our editorial decision-making.Tune into the Fashionista Network to join the conversation with fashion and beauty industry leaders. Sign up here.Subscribe to Our Newsletter",
